    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="329"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3831/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 21, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Department’s telegram No. 64, July 17, 8 p.m. I feel very strongly that it
                    would be advisable to have the conversations conducted in Washington. I also
                    consider that De la Hue’s presence there to assist the Haitian Minister would be
                    advisable. May I suggest to the Haitian Government that his departure about
                    August 2 after the return of Pixley<note n="32" xml:id="d329fn32">Rex A. Pixley,
                        Deputy Fiscal Representative of the Republic of Haiti.</note> would in the
                    opinion of our Government facilitate negotiations in connection with a
                    commercial treaty. I have every reason to believe that the suggestion will be
                    well received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
